    <h1>Tricyclic Antidepressants (TCAs)</h1>
    
    <div class="alert">
        <strong>ECG Warning:</strong> Evaluate the QRS duration. A QRS > 100 msec is predictive of seizures. A QRS > 160 msec is predictive of ventricular arrhythmias. Look for a prominent terminal R wave in lead aVR (> 3 mm).
    </div>

    <h2>Clinical Presentation</h2>
    <p>Causes toxicity via multiple pathways: sodium channel blockade (cardiac), alpha-1 antagonism (hypotension), anticholinergic effects, and GABA antagonism (seizures).</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Anticholinergic Toxidrome:</strong> Tachycardia, hyperthermia, mydriasis, dry skin, urinary retention, delirium.</li>
        <li><strong>Neuro:</strong> Seizures (often rapid onset).</li>
        <li><strong>Cardio:</strong> Hypotension, widened QRS, ventricular tachycardia/fibrillation.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <hr>
    
    <h2>Weight-Based Resuscitation & Antidotes</h2>

    <div class="calc-box">
        <h3>1. Sodium Bicarbonate</h3>
        <p>The sodium load overcomes competitive sodium channel blockade, and the alkalemia decreases TCA binding to the channels. <strong>Indicated for QRS > 100 msec or arrhythmias.</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Dose:</strong> 1 - 2 mEq/kg IV push.</li>
            <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Repeat boluses every 3-5 minutes until QRS narrows and blood pressure improves. Can start an infusion (3 amps in 1L D5W at 150 mL/hr) to maintain pH between 7.45 - 7.55.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="calc-box">
        <h3>2. Seizure Management</h3>
        <p>Seizures worsen acidosis, which radically increases TCA toxicity and arrhythmias.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Benzodiazepines:</strong> Lorazepam 0.05 mg/kg IV or Diazepam 0.1-0.2 mg/kg IV.</li>
            <li><em>Avoid Phenytoin</em> (it also blocks sodium channels).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="calc-box">
        <h3>3. Refractory Hypotension</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Vasopressors:</strong> Norepinephrine 0.05 - 0.1 mcg/kg/min (direct alpha agonist to overcome blockade).</li>
            <li><strong>Lipid Emulsion:</strong> Consider Intralipid 20% (1.5 mL/kg bolus) for cardiovascular collapse unresponsive to bicarb and pressors.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
